Manchester United have confirmed their second and third summer transfers as Erik ten Hag's maiden season as manager grows ever closer. But the Red Devils are still on the market to bolster his squad ahead of the September 1 deadline. On Tuesday, United officially unveiled Christian Eriksen, who has signed a three-year contract after becoming a free agent this summer. A day later, the club presented Lisandro Martinez as their latest stellar defensive signing, with the Argentine joining Feyenoord left-back Tyrell Malacia in reinforcing Ten Hag's back line. But speculation surrounding Barcelona midfielder is still rife as the Dutchman holds onto the hope of reuniting with his priority transfer target. And he's also understood to be eyeing fresh blood in attack amid continuous murmurs over Cristiano Ronaldo's future at Old Trafford. It's been a whirlwind week of transfer activity at United so far, and there's still room for plenty more where that came from... Follow all of today's live developments from Old Trafford with Express Sport below JUST IN:Â Cristiano Ronaldo 'demands Man Utd contract terminated' 